{
  "stem": "9725.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "However, we decorated it each year, and friends would come.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And my parents would invite their non-Jewish friends, and they would come, to drink some wine or some sweets and things like that.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we would go to the temple.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We would dress up for Purim.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I sort of just vaguely remember, perhaps, my parents, and some of my younger uncles and aunts doing it, but it was mostly a children's holiday.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we-- we did dress up for that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, of course, we hated Yom Kippur.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You couldn't eat.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know, and I still hate not eating.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But Hannukah, I think, was-- and Passover-- Passover's really my most favorite holiday.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And Hannukah was also very, very beautiful, with the menorahs and things.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I'd like to tell you, later, a story about a menorah which I have, that I treasure very, very much.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It is very special.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And as a matter of fact, through an incredible miraculous way, I got about 400 family photographs, including my father's shabbos knife, with his writing on it, which I have.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I'm very fortunate to have many things from my family home, where many of my friends don't have as much as, not only a photograph, but not a broken saucer that was in their home.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I was very fortunate to have a number of things which were in my parents' home.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The community in Bielitz was, what, for its day, would probably be called reform.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I would call it conservative, where the community of Biala, which was just across the river, was orthodox.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there was a lot of orthodox Jews there, and people would be wearing the traditional orthodox clothes.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
